<paragraph blockId="46.[189,303,517,543]" box="[189,303,517,543]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,517,543]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,517,543]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,1399,563,625]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Although this species is known from only two females, the unique colour pattern of the mostly pink to red abdomen and the bright yellow distal fore tarsomeres are diagnostic.</paragraph>
